Module: relay
Author: Brian Weiss <brian@epicsol.org>

Description:
   Relays your last sent/received msgs and notices.

Config Variables:
   RELAY_BUFFER_SIZE       - This determines the number of items that
                             will be stored for each type.

Commands:
   clearrelaybuf
     - Clears all the arrays containing your msgs and notices.

   relay <-m|-n|-sm|-sn> [-list|<item#> [<target>]]
     - The first argument determines the type of message. The values
       are as follows:
         '-m'  : msg             '-n'  : notice
         '-sm' : sent_msg        '-sn' : sent_notice
     - If the "-list" option is specified, the list of items available
       to be relayed will be displayed.
     - If no item # is given, the most recent entry will be used.
     - If no target is given, the current window's target ($T) will be used.

   relm [-list|<item#> [<target>]]
     - Passes its arguments to /relay with the '-m' type.

   reln [-list|<item#> [<target>]]
     - Passes its arguments to /relay with the '-n' type.

   relsm [-list|<item#> [<target>]]
     - Passes its arguments to /relay with the '-sm' type.

   relsn [-list|<item#> [<target>]]
     - Passes its arguments to /relay with the '-sn' type.

